		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Psychoneuroimmunology</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Psychoneuroimmunology</b> (PNI) is the study of the interaction between psychological processes and the nervous and immune systems of the human body.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> PNI takes an interdisciplinary approach, incorporating <a href="/wiki/Psychology" title="Psychology">psychology</a>, <a href="/wiki/Neuroscience" title="Neuroscience">neuroscience</a>, <a href="/wiki/Immunology" title="Immunology">immunology</a>, <a href="/wiki/Physiology" title="Physiology">physiology</a>, <a href="/wiki/Pharmacology" title="Pharmacology">pharmacology</a>, <a href="/wiki/Molecular_biology" title="Molecular biology">molecular biology</a>, <a href="/wiki/Psychiatry" title="Psychiatry">psychiatry</a>, <a href="/wiki/Behavioral_medicine" title="Behavioral medicine">behavioral medicine</a>, <a href="/wiki/Infectious_diseases" title="Infectious diseases" class="mw-redirect">infectious diseases</a>, <a href="/wiki/Endocrinology" title="Endocrinology">endocrinology</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Rheumatology" title="Rheumatology">rheumatology</a>.</p>
<p>The main interests of PNI are the interactions between the <a href="/wiki/Central_nervous_system" title="Central nervous system">nervous</a> and <a href="/wiki/Immune" title="Immune" class="mw-redirect">immune</a> systems and the relationships between mental processes and <a href="/wiki/Health" title="Health">health</a>. PNI studies, among other things, the <a href="/wiki/Physiology" title="Physiology">physiological</a> functioning of the neuroimmune system in health and disease; disorders of the neuroimmune system (<a href="/wiki/Autoimmune_diseases" title="Autoimmune diseases" class="mw-redirect">autoimmune diseases</a>; <a href="/wiki/Hypersensitivity" title="Hypersensitivity">hypersensitivities</a>; <a href="/wiki/Immune_deficiency" title="Immune deficiency" class="mw-redirect">immune deficiency</a>); and the physical, chemical and physiological characteristics of the components of the neuroimmune system <a href="/wiki/In_vitro" title="In vitro">in vitro</a>, <a href="/wiki/In_situ" title="In situ">in situ</a>, and <a href="/wiki/In_vivo" title="In vivo">in vivo</a>.</p>
<p>PNI may also be referred to as psychoendoneuroimmunology (PENI).</p>
