<p><a name="Recommended_Reading" id="Recommended_Reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Psychoneuroimmunology&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Recommended Reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Recommended Reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Berczi and Szentivanyi (2003) <i>NeuroImmune Biology</i>, Elsevier, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0444508511" class="internal">ISBN 0-444-50851-1</a> (Written for the highly technical reader)</li>
<li>Goodkin, Karl, and Adriaan P. Visser, (eds), <i>Psychoneuroimmunology: Stress, Mental Disorders , and Health</i>, American Psychiatric Press, 2000, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0880481714" class="internal">ISBN 0-88048-171-4</a>, technical.</li>
<li>Ransohoff, Richard, et al. (eds), <i>Universes in Delicate Balance: Chemokines and the Nervous System</i>, Elsevier, 2002, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0444510028" class="internal">ISBN 0-444-51002-8</a></li>
<li>Robert Ader, David L. Felten, Nicholas Cohen , <i>Psychoneuroimmunology</i>, 4th edition, 2 volumes, Academic Press, (2006), <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/012088576X" class="internal">ISBN 0-12-088576-X</a></li>
<li>Roberts, Thomas B. (2006). "Do Entheogen-induced Mystical Experiences Boost the Immune System?: Psychedelics, Peak Experiences, and Wellness." Chapter 6 in <i>Psychedelic Horizons</i>. Westport, CT: Praeger/Greenwood.</li>
</ul>
